### Customer Support Ticket System — sample requests
### Open this file in VSCode with REST Client extension or JetBrains HTTP Client.

@host = http://localhost:8000
@ticketId = REPLACE-WITH-UUID-AFTER-CREATING

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Health check
GET {{host}}/healthz

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Create ticket
POST {{host}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "cust-1",
  "customer_email": "alice@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Alice",
  "subject": "Cannot login",
  "description": "I am unable to log in. This is critical, production down.",
  "tags": ["login", "p0"],
  "metadata": {"source": "web_form", "browser": "Chrome 121", "device_type": "desktop"}
}

### Create ticket WITH automatic classification
POST {{host}}/tickets?auto_classify=true
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "cust-2",
  "customer_email": "bob@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Bob",
  "subject": "Refund request for invoice 12345",
  "description": "I would like a refund. The charge on my subscription was duplicated."
}

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### List all tickets
GET {{host}}/tickets

### List with category filter
GET {{host}}/tickets?category=billing_question

### List with combined filters + pagination
GET {{host}}/tickets?priority=urgent&status=new&limit=10&offset=0

### List by customer
GET {{host}}/tickets?customer_id=cust-1

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Get single ticket
GET {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}

### Get non-existent ticket (expect 404)
GET {{host}}/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Partial update
PUT {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress",
  "assigned_to": "agent-007"
}

### Manual override of auto-classified fields
PUT {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "feature_request",
  "priority": "low"
}

### Resolve
PUT {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "resolved"
}

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Auto-classify existing ticket
POST {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/auto-classify

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Bulk import from CSV
POST {{host}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

< ../tests/fixtures/sample_tickets.csv
------boundary--

### Bulk import — JSON
POST {{host}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.json"
Content-Type: application/json

< ../tests/fixtures/sample_tickets.json
------boundary--

### Bulk import — XML
POST {{host}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.xml"
Content-Type: application/xml

< ../tests/fixtures/sample_tickets.xml
------boundary--

### Bulk import — invalid (expect failed=3, successful=0)
POST {{host}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="invalid_tickets.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

< ../tests/fixtures/invalid_tickets.csv
------boundary--

### -----------------------------------------------------------------
### Delete
DELETE {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}
